# @VERSION spec:gdls v:0.1.0 generated:2026-03-04 source:schema-agent
# @FORMAT COLUMN|SQL_TYPE|NULLABLE|KEY|DESCRIPTION
# Project Atlas — reverse-engineered legacy finance schema (as-is)

@D legacy_finance|Acme legacy ledger schema (Postgres 11) — produced by schema-agent reverse engineering

@T GeneralLedger|Account master — root of the legacy ledger
GL_ACCOUNT_ID|INTEGER|N|PK|Primary key
GL_CODE|VARCHAR(20)|N||Account code (chart of accounts)
GL_TEXT_1|VARCHAR(50)|Y||Primary account name
GL_TEXT_2|VARCHAR(50)|Y||Secondary description (often unused)
GL_STATUS|VARCHAR(20)|N||Account lifecycle status
GL_PARENT_ID|INTEGER|Y|FK|Parent account (hierarchy)
GL_CURRENCY|CHAR(3)|N||ISO 4217 currency code
GL_CREATED_AT|TIMESTAMP|N||Row creation timestamp
GL_UPDATED_AT|TIMESTAMP|Y||Last mutation timestamp
@E GeneralLedger.GL_STATUS|ACTIVE,INACTIVE,SUSPENDED,ARCHIVED|Account lifecycle status

@T JournalEntry|Journal entries posted against GeneralLedger accounts
JE_ID|BIGINT|N|PK|Primary key
JE_DATE|DATE|N||Posting date
JE_ACCOUNT_REF|INTEGER|N|FK|Account reference
JE_AMOUNT|DECIMAL(18,4)|N||Posted amount in account currency
JE_FX_RATE|DECIMAL(12,6)|Y||Snapshot FX rate used for translation
JE_SOURCE|VARCHAR(20)|N||How the entry originated
JE_CREATED_BY|VARCHAR(50)|N||System or user that posted
JE_REVERSED_BY|BIGINT|Y|FK|Reversing entry (if any)
JE_BATCH_ID|VARCHAR(40)|Y|FK|Batch identifier for reconciliation
@E JournalEntry.JE_SOURCE|MANUAL,AUTO,REVERSAL,IMPORT,FX_REVAL|Origin of the journal entry

@T PaymentBatch|Batches feeding into the ledger from PaymentService
PB_ID|VARCHAR(40)|N|PK|Batch identifier
PB_RUN_AT|TIMESTAMP|N||When the batch ran
PB_STATUS|VARCHAR(20)|N||Batch processing state
PB_ENTRY_COUNT|INTEGER|N||Number of entries in batch
PB_FAILED_COUNT|INTEGER|Y||Failures recorded during processing
@E PaymentBatch.PB_STATUS|PENDING,PROCESSING,COMPLETED,FAILED,RECONCILED

@T Customer|Customer master replicated from Salesforce nightly
CUST_ID|VARCHAR(40)|N|PK|External customer identifier
CUST_NAME|VARCHAR(120)|N||Display name
CUST_TIER|VARCHAR(20)|Y||Service tier
CUST_REGION|VARCHAR(40)|Y||Operational region
CUST_SF_SYNC_AT|TIMESTAMP|Y||Last Salesforce sync
@E Customer.CUST_TIER|STRATEGIC,ENTERPRISE,MID,SMB

@T ReconciliationRun|Per-period reconciliation job results
REC_ID|BIGINT|N|PK|Primary key
REC_PERIOD|VARCHAR(7)|N||YYYY-MM period
REC_STARTED_AT|TIMESTAMP|N||When reconciliation began
REC_COMPLETED_AT|TIMESTAMP|Y||When reconciliation finished
REC_VARIANCE|DECIMAL(18,4)|Y||Total unreconciled variance
REC_STATUS|VARCHAR(20)|N||Reconciliation outcome
@E ReconciliationRun.REC_STATUS|SUCCESS,VARIANCE,FAILED,IN_PROGRESS

@T AuditLog|Append-only audit trail (currently truncated annually — non-compliant)
AUDIT_ID|BIGINT|N|PK|Primary key
AUDIT_TS|TIMESTAMP|N||Event timestamp
AUDIT_ACTOR|VARCHAR(80)|Y||Acting user or service (often null in legacy)
AUDIT_ENTITY|VARCHAR(40)|N||Entity name affected
AUDIT_ENTITY_ID|VARCHAR(80)|N||Entity primary key
AUDIT_OP|VARCHAR(10)|N||Operation type
@E AuditLog.AUDIT_OP|INSERT,UPDATE,DELETE,REVERSE

@R JournalEntry.JE_ACCOUNT_REF -> GeneralLedger.GL_ACCOUNT_ID|fk|Journal entry to account
@R JournalEntry.JE_REVERSED_BY -> JournalEntry.JE_ID|fk|Self-referential reversal
@R JournalEntry.JE_BATCH_ID -> PaymentBatch.PB_ID|fk|Entry to source batch
@R GeneralLedger.GL_PARENT_ID -> GeneralLedger.GL_ACCOUNT_ID|fk|Account hierarchy
@R PaymentBatch.PB_ID -> ReconciliationRun.REC_ID|reconciles|Batch reconciliation linkage
